<p>Notice how the 20-day (green) dropped below the 200 first — that was the early warning. Then the 50-day followed and confirmed with the Death Cross. By the time you see this, the bearish thesis is strong. This is where Ed's PUTS strategy comes in.</p>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h3>6. Price Rejected at a Moving Average</h3>

<p>When a stock is falling and tries to rally back up to the 50 or 200-day MA but gets <strong>rejected</strong>, that MA has become resistance. The floor is now the ceiling — same concept as support & resistance, but moving with time.</p>

