  <text x="208" y="108" fill="#f85149" font-size="11" font-family="Inter,sans-serif" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">REJECTED</text>

  <circle cx="450" cy="134" r="10" fill="none" stroke="#f85149" stroke-width="2"/>
  <text x="450" y="118" fill="#f85149" font-size="11" font-family="Inter,sans-serif" font-weight="700" text-anchor="middle">REJECTED</text>

  <!-- Arrows showing rejection -->
  <path d="M208,135 L208,152" stroke="#f85149" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
  <polygon points="208,157 203,149 213,149" fill="#f85149"/>
  <path d="M450,144 L450,161" stroke="#f85149" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
  <polygon points="450,166 445,158 455,158" fill="#f85149"/>

  <!-- Labels -->
  <text x="655" y="96" fill="#f85149" font-size="12" font-family="Inter,sans-serif" font-weight="600">200 MA</text>
  <text x="655" y="146" fill="#58a6ff" font-size="12" font-family="Inter,sans-serif" font-weight="600">50 MA</text>
  <text x="655" y="246" fill="#e6edf3" font-size="12" font-family="Inter,sans-serif" font-weight="500" opacity="0.7">Price</text>

  <rect x="180" y="252" width="340" height="22" rx="5" fill="rgba(248,81,73,0.1)"/>
  <text x="350" y="268" fill="#f85149" font-size="12" font-family="Inter,sans-serif" font-weight="600" text-anchor="middle">50 MA flipped from SUPPORT to RESISTANCE</text>
</svg>

<p>Each rejection confirms the MA as a ceiling. Price tries to break through, fails, and falls harder. This is a strong signal to stay in or add to PUT positions.</p>

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->
<h2>The MA Squeeze — Trend Change Warning</h2>
<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════ -->

<p>One more critical pattern: when all three MAs start <strong>squeezing together</strong>, it means the current trend is losing steam and a reversal may be coming. Wide spread = strong trend. MAs converging = get ready for a shift.</p>

