<div class="callout warning">
  <div class="callout-title">Key Questions to Ask Every Time You Look at Your Chart</div>
  <p><strong>1. What order are the MAs in?</strong> 20 above 50 above 200 = bullish. Reversed = bearish.<br/>
  <strong>2. Are they spreading apart or squeezing?</strong> Spreading = trend strengthening. Squeezing = possible reversal ahead.<br/>
  <strong>3. Where is price relative to the MAs?</strong> Above all 3 = strong bull. Below all 3 = strong bear. Between them = choppy.<br/>
  <strong>4. Is price bouncing off or getting rejected at any MA?</strong> That tells you which MA is acting as support or resistance.</p>
